     6	## Seven resolutions
     7	
     8	1. **§10.6 vs §17.2 contradiction (urgent-drain decision world).** Implement W0
     9	   decisions PLUS per-live-deferred-world expansion: on urgent drains,
    10	   re-validate/expand every live deferred world's memos.
    11	2. **§9.8 "urgent writes skip the walk" is UNSOUND.** An equal-value urgent write
    12	   onto a tape never propagates via the kernel yet shifts every pending world's
    13	   fold. Applied logged writes must ALWAYS queue a token-0 walk.
    14	3. **First-divergence completeness gap.** An urgent write can CAUSE first
    15	   divergence for world k (branch flip onto k's entries) with no k-memo existing.
    16	   Closed by the same per-live-deferred-world expansion as (1).
    17	4. **Truncation re-notification.** Truncation must re-notify the rolled-back
    18	   batch's lane (spec is silent; otherwise the lane is stale until an unrelated
    19	   drain).
    20	5. **Unmarked-nested-child certificate hole.** Overlay frames must ALWAYS recurse
    21	   via overlayEvaluate — never take the kernel path for children inside an
    22	   overlay frame — else unlogged grandchild sources escape the parent
    23	   certificate.
    24	6. **Fork double: onBatchOpened edge.** §9.1 needs it; §6.1 lacks it. Add
    25	   onBatchOpened to the fork-double interface.
    26	7. **Minor.** (a) Stamp ONE retire-time ticket per retirement (not per entry).
    27	   (b) Missing-world broadcast default = current W0, with subscription-time
    28	   seeding of live deferred worlds.
