    38	## Async model (owner design change, 2026-07-08): Solid-2.0-adapted graph-status suspense
    39	
    40	Deviations from spec §11.3/§12.3, adopted per the owner brief (reference:
    41	vendor/solid/packages/solid-signals/src/core/{async,core}.ts):
    42	
    43	1. **Pending/error are graph state, not evaluation-attempt state.** The §11.3
    44	   boxes remain the value-space representation, but a computed hitting an
    45	   unresolved async dep now EVALUATES-TO-PENDING: no thrown thenables
    46	   mid-evaluation. `ctx.use` records the pending thenable on the active
    47	   evaluation frame and RETURNS (undefined stand-in), so multiple `ctx.use`
    48	   calls in one evaluation all register before pending surfaces — parallel
    49	   fetches, no throw-created waterfalls.
    50	2. **Thenable identity is node×world, not render-attempt.** §12.3's
    51	   lineage-keyed positional cache is DELETED (with the react bridge's
    52	   synthesized per-container lineage and its interleaved-works aliasing
    53	   limitation). Slots key on: `canon` for canonical evaluations, the pass
    54	   INCLUDE MASK for pass worlds (stable across restarts/retries of one
    55	   logical work; distinct for works with different batch sets — identical
    56	   batch sets are the same world, where sharing is correct), writer token
    57	   for writer worlds, `n` for newest.
    58	3. **Downstream forwards pending by default**: reading a pending computed
    59	   inside another evaluation records the store-held thenable on the reader's
    60	   frame and continues with undefined; the reader's own result becomes the
    61	   pending box. Errors keep §11.3 throw-through-read semantics (caught by
    62	   the wrapper into error state).
    63	4. **Settlement is a normal write**: resolution commits through
    64	   invalidate → propagate (+ the §10.5 epoch bump for world memos).
    65	   Resumption is propagation.
    66	5. **Latest-wins while pending; first-wins once settled.** A pending slot
    67	   occupant is REPLACED by a different incoming thenable (re-evaluations are
    68	   dirty/cert-gated, so a different thenable at a pending position means the
    69	   inputs moved — found by the interleaved-works RTL case: a canonical
    70	   evaluation after an input change must not stay stuck on the stale
    71	   in-flight fetch). Settled occupants stay until the canonical
    72	   settled-completion clear (fresh fetches on the next real input change).
    73	   Cache-less callers may pay one extra fetch per settlement wave; keyed
    74	   data layers make replacement a no-op.
    75	6. `ctx.use` outside a computed evaluation throws (it previously threw a
    76	   raw SUSPEND sentinel through the caller).
