   212	## AMBIENT VISIBILITY DIVERGENCE (owner-approved; alt family ONLY)
   213	
   214	**THE RULE** (deliberate, recorded divergence — mainline cosignal keeps
   215	NEWEST-ambient; never port either family's expectation into the other's
   216	suite):
   217	
   218	1. Ambient top-level/handler/effect reads (`.state`) = **W0** (committed +
   219	   applied urgent). Pending DEFERRED batches are INVISIBLE outside their
   220	   own context until commit.
   221	2. Inside a deferred batch's own scope (open transition write scope) or
   222	   its render pass: that batch's world — read-your-own-draft preserved;
   223	   urgent/batch() read-own-writes unchanged (conformance-critical).
   224	3. The READ FAMILY:
   225	   - `.state`        → real      (W0; drafts hidden)
   226	   - `latest(x)`     → intent    (Wn incl. drafts; per-context table, rule 10)
   227	   - `committed(x)`  → on screen (per-root committed views; + useCommitted)
   228	   - `isPending(x)`  → loading   (flip-only probe)
   229	
   230	**WHY**: (a) React-model alignment — a pending transition's lane state is
   231	invisible to urgent handlers in React itself; (b) speculation-leak
   232	elimination — an urgent write derived from `.state` during a pending
   233	transition must not bake the draft into the committed lineage (the abort
   234	case would leave contamination; see the write-gate (v) tests and the
   235	pinned oracle scenario); (c) harmony with the context-sensitive suspense
   236	rule (7a): both make "inside the transition" the only place its
   237	speculative state is observable.
   238	
   239	**PERF NOTE**: ambient reads with only urgent (applied) tapes now take the
   240	kernel fast path outright — unapplied deferred entries no longer force
   241	overlay folds on unrelated ambient reads (fast-path hits increase;
   242	measured G-8 movement reported in the landing report).

