The protocol can now be reduced to seven semantic operations: current batch, run in batch, fresh-pass enter, render-callstack exit/resume, pass end, per-root batch commit, and batch retirement. The current API carries several unused dimensions—mutation windows, discard-all, generation numbers, dispositions, fallback allocation, multiple listeners—that do not reach alt-a. I’m checking the original protocol and test-plan text now so the report distinguishes “not consumed” from “safe to remove.”
