   787	### 6.5 Batch entanglement (`unstable_runInBatch`)
   788	
   789	The problem this solves: a component can subscribe to a signal *after* a
   790	pending deferred batch already wrote to it (the component mounted, or first
   791	read the signal, in the gap between that batch's write and this component's
   792	commit). The component must now be re-rendered *as part of that batch* — its
   793	corrective update has to render with the batch's other updates and commit in
   794	the same frame. Wrapping the corrective `setState` in a fresh
   795	`startTransition` is **not** enough: `startTransition` starts a *new*
   796	transition, which may be assigned a different lane, render separately, and
   797	commit at a different time. A frame could commit where the batch's other
   798	components show the new world and this component shows the old one — a tear
   799	we introduced ourselves. Only the reconciler knows which lanes a batch
   800	occupies, so only the fork can offer this operation.
