   849	mutation-effects flush, not in `commitRoot`, because with View Transitions
   850	the mutation phase runs later, inside the browser's `startViewTransition`
   851	update callback; the bracket fires only when mutations will actually occur,
   852	and covers every commit path including `flushSync`. Scope is React's
   853	*reconciliation* mutations. Documented exclusions callers must filter
   854	themselves: the layout-phase `<img src>` re-assignment, suspensey-CSS
   855	`<link>` insertion, imperative Float APIs (`preload`/`preinit`), View
   856	Transition name attributes, and DOM writes from user effect code.
