+One current allocation bug falls out of this inventory: `ambientScopeWorld` explicitly wants a non-minting probe (`packages/cosignals-alt-a/src/engine.ts:1573-1582`), but the real bridge implements it by calling the minting `unstable_getCurrentWriteBatch` (`packages/cosignals-alt-a/src/react/bridge.ts:156-159`). While any deferred batch is live, an ambient read can therefore mint an urgent batch and schedule its close microtask. `currentBatch(false)` removes both the semantic mismatch and the allocation.
